{{date|January 21, 2015}}
[[File:Kyiv. Peace march 18 january 2014 24.JPG|thumb|left|"I am - Volnovakha". Peace march in memory of victims of People's Republic of Donetsk in Kyiv]]
{{Ukraine}}
Thousands of [[Ukraine|Ukrainians]] in [[Kyiv]] took part on Sunday in marches in memory of reported victims of {{w|Donetsk People's Republic}} militants in a tragedy on January 13 near {{w|Volnovakha}} in [[Donetsk Oblast]]. On that day reportedly thirteen people on a bus were killed and sixteen wounded when separatists struck the bus with a {{w|BM-21 Grad|Grad missile launcher}} near a Ukrainian checkpoint.

The same marches also took place in other major Ukrainian cities, including {{w|Odessa}}, {{w|Kharkiv}}, {{w|Dniepropetrovsk}} and {{w|Zaporizhia}}<!-- (1) --> as well as some towns in Donetsk and {{w|Luhansk Oblast|Luhansk regions}}<!-- (2) --> under Ukrainian control<!-- (3) -->. 

During the march in Kyiv President [[Petro Poroshenko|Poroshenko]] promised to return {{w|Donbass}} to Ukraine<!-- (4) -->, while participants in {{w|Lutsk}}<!-- (5) --> and {{w|Khmelnytskyi, Ukraine|Khmelnytsky}}<!-- (6) --> requested the Goverment to recognise Donetsk People's Republic and {{w|Luhansk People's Republic}} as terrorist organisations officially.  Mayor of Kiev {{w|Vitali Klitschko}} said, {{translated quote|uk|Ukrainian language|Сюди прийшли ті, кому не байдужа проблема тероризму. Ті, хто хоче зупинити це зло.|Here are those, who are disturbed with a problem of terrorism. Those who want to stop this evil.}}<!-- (7) -->

The march ended with a public prayer for victims of terror<!-- (8) --><!-- (9) -->. The Major Archbishop of the Ukrainian Greek Catholic Church {{w|Sviatoslav Shevchuk}} and the Patriarch of Kyiv and All Rus’ - Ukraine {{w|Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret}}, as well as representatives of {{w|Ukrainian Orthodox Church (Moscow Patriarchate)|Ukrainian Orthodox Church}}, {{w|Ukrainian Autocephalous Orthodox Church}}, {{w|Clerical Board of Ukraine's Muslims}}, {{w|Armenian Apostolic Church}} took part in this prayer<!-- (9) -->.

{{haveyoursay}}

